observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed that:
The Municipal Treasurer strictly require the check claimants to fill up completely the Box E of the Disbursement Vouchers;
The Municipal Treasurer furnish the Accounting Office the Monthly RCI together with the schedule of unreleased checks;
The Municipal Accountant record the transaction only upon the receipt of the RCI from the Treasury Office.

2.10		We recommended that the Management:
require the GSO to practice the use of Request and Issue Slip (RIS) in every issuance of inventory item to the end-users.  Also, submit the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (RSMI) on a weekly basis to the Accountant in order to prepare the corresponding JEV to record the supplies and materials issued/consumed as expense;
require the CGSO to maintain an updated Stock Cards of inventories, and to conduct periodic reconciliation of their records with the Ledger Cards of the Accounting;
direct the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory-taking of supplies and materials every six (6) months the duly certified   Report on the Physical Count of Inventories for each type of inventory and shall be submitted to the Office of the Auditor not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively, as required; and
require the Accountant to prepare the necessary JEVs to adjust and establish the correct inventory items per books as well as the actual office supplies expense based on the result of the physical inventory taking and the issued office supplies.

In all procurement related activities of the Municipality, we recommend strict compliance with the provisions of RA 9184 and the revised IRR, specifically on the following:
Preparation of the Procurement Monitoring Report by the Bids and Awards Committee for approval by the Head of the Procuring Entity and submission of the same to the GPPB in printed and electronic format within fourteen (14) calendar days after the end of each semester;

Direct the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly comply with the provisions of Section 20.1 paragraph f of the revised IRR of RA 9184 that is to reiterate and emphasize the importance of confidentiality and the applicable sanctions and penalties, as well as agree on measures to ensure compliance with the foregoing;

Direct the posting of the Notice of Award and the Notice to Proceed to PhilGEPS as required in Section 39 of this revised IRR; and

BAC should require the winning bidders to submit the appropriate format of certification by the Insurance Commission authorizing the surety or insurance company to issue such performance security; and

To minimize the commission of errors or omission of significant procedures, we suggest that the BAC utilize the prescribed Philippine Bidding Documents (PBDs) for the procurement of goods and services, infrastructure and consulting services.     Complete and sufficient bidding documents must be prepared for it determines the validity and propriety of the procurement transactions entered into by the City Government. No contract shall be executed unless all necessary bidding requirements are complied with to facilitate auditorial and technical evaluation review of the contracts.

